1.title: The Power Up 1000

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: The hosts get a hold of a mysterious machine that claims to give the user the ability to achieve video game power ups in real life, but it's not all it's cracked up to be.

2.title: We Have a Llama

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: When the Gaming Show gang see a dip in their views, they decide it's time to spice things up with a new mascot for the garage - a live Alpaca.

3.title: The Glitch

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: When spill in the garage causes Jesse's teleportation abilities to go on the fritz and damages the consoles' "save" function, Jesse winds up in Europe while Julia and Ian must beat a game in one sitting.

4.title: Crowdfunding

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: With the equipment in the garage falling apart, the gang decides to rip a page out of the indie game world's book and start a crowdfunding campaign.

5.title: Company Man

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: When Ian leaves the garage to pursue his dream job at EA, Julia and Jesse feel they must pick up their socks and attempt to fulfill all their biggest gaming goals all at once.

6.title: Extreme

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: In an effort to spice up the channel, the hosts decide to re-brand Gaming Show with a more "extreme" format.

7.title: the Movie

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

7.plot: In an effort to make the garage vids more "cinematic", Ian decides to write and direct his own video-game inspired opus: Pong the movie.

8.title: Garage Sale

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

8.plot: When the gang's garage sale proves to be a bust, they must use their gaming prowess to rope in the sales help of Toronto Blue Jays starting pitcher Drew Hutchison.

9.title: Wagony Redux: Electric Boogaloo

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

9.plot: When Jesse's Uncle drops off his 2-seater convertible smack dab in the middle of the garage, the hosts must work around it to make their channel work.

10.title: Shaqowe'en

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

10.plot: After he insults Shaq-Fu on the channel, Ian is summoned to Shaq's mansion in Orlando, while Julia takes over Halloween duties in the garage and Jesse becomes a video game voice actor.

11.title: Time-Out

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

11.plot: Jesse goes to DeMar DeRozan to get advice on how to win video games, but soon starts borrowing DeMar's stuff without asking and then realizes he's taking advantage of his new friend.

12.title: Hall of Fame

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

12.plot: Ian goes to the Video Game Hall of Fame to see if he can get inducted for his recent victories. Back at the garage, Jesse and Julia stretch the meaning of "Hall of Fame" to the limits.

13.title: Tournie

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

13.plot: Jesse, Julia & Ian host a tournament in the garage, but show that they have a lot to learn. Jesse goes to the Nintendo World Championships to get tips on better tournament-hosting.

14.title: Rock & Roll

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

14.plot: Jesse, Julia & Ian receive criticism for their Rock Band Let's Play, and get tips on how to improve their style from rock star Andrew WK.

15.title: Sponsorship

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

15.plot: Julia and Ian shoot a commercial for a sponsor without telling Jesse. When Jesse finds out, he decides to leave the garage and start his own channel in his parents' backyard.

16.title: All Gamers Day

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

16.plot: The Gaming Show gang decide to create their own video game themed holiday called All Gamers Day. They have fun shooting their very own holiday special. Featuring The Tenors

17.title: iRoboto

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

17.plot: The Gaming Show gang decide to build a robot but they end up with more than they bargained for when their Artificially Intelligent Gaming Robot begins to take over the garage.

18.title: Gaming Show Olympics

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

18.plot: The Gaming Show gang holds its first ever Gaming Show Olympics. Only the best will make it through all the video game events to win the Gaming Show Gold medal.

19.title: Reach for the Tabletop

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

19.plot: The Gaming Show gang decides to make their own video game themed board game. They enlist the help of some board game experts but can't stop pranking each other.

20.title: How Bizarro

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

20.plot: The Gaming Show gang discovers a bizarro copycat gaming channel called the Showing Game. They challenge the bizarro garage to a multiplayer showdown. Featuring Masi Oka.

21.title: Top Fun

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

21.plot: Jesse's reckless style in flight simulators is causing friction in the garage and leads to him losing his confidence, but a trip to a flight simulator academy gets him back on track.

22.title: Japan-O-Ramic

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

22.plot: Jesse's mother has cleaned up the garage without him knowing, and accidentally given away his prized collector's edition copy of Earthbound. Refusing to let it go, Jesse travels to Japan to find the game and put it back in its rightful place.

23.title: Arcade Machine

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

23.plot: The trusty ol' arcade machine in the corner of the garage breaks down and while it's out being fixed Jesse tries to replace it with something different. Julia and Ian are opposed because as they see it, the machine is a part of the family.

24.title: Gaming Show in My Everywhere

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

24.plot: The garage has been taken over by mice so while Jesse's parents are clearing the rodents out of the area, the gang decides to split up with handheld game consoles and find the coolest places they can think of to play.

25.title: Showdown

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

25.plot: The garage will play host to a battle between two professional gamers, Nakat and Keitaro. After setting up a livestream and promoting it to their fans, Jesse, Julia and Ian watch and commentate while the two masters go at it.

1.title: URL Not Earl

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Jesse must become a hero on a visit to Legoland, Julia races the national karting champ at MarioKart, and Ian calls on NBA stars Terrence Ross and Jordan Hamilton to take a trip down memory lane with old school NBA Jam. With a little help from internet pals like ThinkNoodles, the gang launches the Gaming Show Youtube channel.

2.title: Code Yellow

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Things at the garage heat up when the spirit of friendly competition takes over as Jesse calls on his buddy, baseball star Brett Lawrie, for a few tips, while Julia's Pokemon passion reaches a whole new level when Pikachu himself gets involved, and Ian takes on a few Major League Soccer pros with gusto.

3.title: The Gimmick

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Inspired by fellow youtubers like FinsGraphics and Captain Sparklez, the Gaming Show gang decides to shake up their own channel with a gimmick. Julia visits the minds behind the app MegaJump at Get Some Games, Jesse teleports to a San Francisco recording studio to meet Charles Martinet - the legendary voice of Mario, and Metallica's Rob Trujillo does the kids a favour by reviewing Pacman and the Ghostly Adventures 2.

4.title: DIY

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Ian goes undercover as a luchador to get the scoop on indie hit Guacamelee, Jesse risks getting caught in a temporal rift to check out Disney's Infinity 2.0, and with the garage to herself, Julia finally has the chance to kick back, build her own virtual reality simulator and travel inside her favorite games.

5.title: My Uncle's Car

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: Gaming Show is turned upside down when Jesse's uncle's station wagon appears in the middle of the garage. With no room to game around the car, and no driver's licenses to speak of, chaos naturally ensues as the gang calls on pals like The Diamond Minecart and Kirby himself to help them get "Gaming Show In My Uncle's Car in My Parent's Garage" off the ground.

6.title: The Troll

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: Ian catches up with Toronto Blue Jay pitcher Marcus Stroman who helps him review MLB15. Back at the garage, the kids discover that a mysterious internet troll has been dissing their videos, so they seek advice from Youtube acapella star Smooth McGroove, and game voice-over legend Nolan North, as Jesse puts his hockey chops to the test with NHL15 at EA Sports in Seattle, and his Pokemon skills come under fire in an old-west duel, all while the troll is revealed.

7.title: All Night Long!

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

7.plot: The hosts are jacked up to stay up all night to raise funds for the Children's Miracle Network Hospitals by hosting their very own 24-hour Extra Life gaming challenge. But as the gang games on into the night, things start to get trippy when Julia and Ian discover Jesse's become full-blown rockstar after playing too much Rocksmith in his sleep and their Mii Maker characters take on a life of their own. British gaming/Youtube sensation YogsCast give a tour of Yogs Towers, the gang also learns about Fifa15 with professional footballers in Vancouver, and Julia visits ...

8.title: The Intern

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

8.plot: The crew decides to bring on an intern and end up with 7 foot tall, NBA star, Jonas Valciunas. Meanwhile, Jesse heads to PopCap Games to check out the new Plants vs Zombies shooter getting a surprise of his own, and sneaks past security at Insomniac Games grabbing a glimpse of the yet-to-be-released installment of Ratchet and Clank. Back at the garage the kids discover that, while a welcome addition to the team, Jonas lacks some of the basic skills needed to be an intern on a game specific Youtube channel: namely any gaming skills. Maybe it's time for a trade?

9.title: Back in Time

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

9.plot: When every single console in the garage breaks at once, the Gaming Show gang has to get creative with some old school gaming. From Super Nintendo to Atari, the host's play their way through a history of gaming all the way into the future of gaming tech: the Occulus Rift virtual simulator. Rock stars Ian and Aaron from Billy Talent guest with their own retro review of EA's NHL '95.

10.title: Cry Wolf

episode of.title: Gaming Show (In My Parents Garage) (TV Series 2014– )

10.plot: As the first season of Gaming Show comes to a close, the hosts decide to cash in the last of their celebrity favours. Show contributor The Diamond Minecart shows up with some helpful MineCraft tips, Ian gets a Just Dance lesson from Gaming Show's favourite Olympian - Patrick Chan, Donkey Kong stops by to smash up the garage and cheer on the gang in Tropical Freeze, and Jesse gets accused of crying wolf when he insists he can bag an interview with Adam Sandler.
